sections.text: county of Howard is bounded as follows: Commencing at the southwest corner of township thirteen, north, of range twelve, west; thence east to the southeast corner of township thirteen, north, of range nine, west; thence north to the northeast corner of township sixteen, north, of range nine, west; thence west to the northwest corner of township sixteen, north, of range twelve, west; thence south to the place of beginning.SourceG.S.1873, c. 12, § 28, p. 217;R.S.1913, § 860;C.S.1922, § 762;C.S.1929, § 25-149;R.S.1943, § 22-147.

22-147.Howard.

The county of Howard is bounded as follows: Commencing at the southwest corner of township thirteen, north, of range twelve, west; thence east to the southeast corner of township thirteen, north, of range nine, west; thence north to the northeast corner of township sixteen, north, of range nine, west; thence west to the northwest corner of township sixteen, north, of range twelve, west; thence south to the place of beginning.

SourceG.S.1873, c. 12, § 28, p. 217;R.S.1913, § 860;C.S.1922, § 762;C.S.1929, § 25-149;R.S.1943, § 22-147.
